# Security Rules — CareerOS Campus AI

## Authentication

- JWT via `python-jose`. Secret from `config.JWT_SECRET` (env var only — never hardcoded).
- Bearer token scheme. Verified in `services/core-api/app/dependencies.py::current_user`.
- `role` claim in JWT: `student` | `officer` | `admin`. Gate at dependency level, not in route logic.
- Session tokens in `session_tokens` table — invalidate on logout.

## Authorisation

- Every protected route: `Depends(current_user)`.
- Officer routes: additionally assert `user.role == "officer"` at the dependency level.
- College-scoped RBAC: officers see only their college's data. Never trust college ID from the frontend.
- `resume_evidence` proof URIs: gated by college-scoped RBAC — never broadly accessible.

## Data / PII (DPDP-aware)

- Separate raw PII from scoring / analytics tables.
- `events_audit` payloads: never log names, emails, or file content — log entity IDs only.
- File uploads: validate MIME type + file size before parsing. Reject non-PDF/DOCX.
- Explicit consent captured before resume processing.
- Retention schedule by graduating batch — deletion endpoint required before production.

## Secrets hygiene

- Never commit secrets — not in `.env`, not in comments, not in migration files.
- Rotate any secret that touched version control, no matter how briefly.
- `.env.example` contains placeholder values only (already enforced — see repo pattern).
- `config.py` uses `os.getenv()` — safe dev fallbacks for non-secret config only.

## Input safety

- Parameterised queries only. SQLAlchemy ORM handles this — never raw SQL with f-strings.
- Pydantic v2 validates all request bodies at the boundary.
- Never execute or eval uploaded file content.
- Never leak stack traces to clients — catch at route edge, return safe `HTTPException`.

## AI rewriter guardrails (critical)

- `services/ai-rewriter` must NEVER invent metrics, team size, tools, certifications, or internships.
- Every rewrite suggestion carries `evidence_ids[]` pointing to source resume sections.
- Claims without evidence → `unsupported_claims[]` — never silently included in `section_rewrites[]`.
- User confirms `requires_confirmation[]` items before they are applied.
- Any fabrication incident: postmortem + new rule in `.obsidian-ai-memory/03-ERRORS/anti-patterns.md`.
